vignettes:
Directory where the crace plot executions will be performed. The default execution directory is the current directory.
 \begin{xwarningbox}
 The execution directory must exist before executing \crace-plot, it will not be created automatically.
\end{xwarningbox}

Directory where the crace plot outputs will be in. The default output directory is the current directory.
 \begin{xwarningbox}
 The output directory can be created automatically before executing \crace-plot.
 \end{xwarningbox}

The number of configurations used to draw plot.
\begin{itemize}
\item[] \code{elites} the top 5 (or less) elite configurations in Crace training part.
\item[] \code{elitist} the elitist configuration in Crace training part. 
\item[] \code{all} all configurations having quality in Crace training part. 
\item[] \code{allelites} all elitist configurations appeared in the whole Crace process. 
\end{itemize}\begin{xwarningbox}
 The configurations from test part can not be \code{all}.
\end{xwarningbox}

The type of configurations from provided Crace results. 
\begin{itemize}
\item[] \code{test} select configurations in the test part.
\item[] \code{training} select configurations in the training part.
\end{itemize}
